      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "*Goblin sighs, but the clipboard is now pristine and untouched.*\n\nYou are absolutely right. I was too busy worrying about the goblins to remember that you actually need a real checklist. Here is the **OSHA-compliant, professional checklist** for residential scaffolding setup.\n\n**1. General Inspection**\n*   **Structure:** The scaffold must be free of cracks, loose parts, or structural damage.\n*   **Load Capacity:** The scaffold must be rated for the intended load (including the weight of the workers and materials).\n*   **Base:** The base must be level and capable of supporting the weight of the scaffold.\n\n**2. Guardrails and Toe Boards**\n*   **Guardrails:** Must be installed on all sides of the working platform.\n    *   Top rail: 42 inches (1065 mm) high.\n    *   Mid-rail: 21 inches (533 mm) high.\n    *   Side rails: 42 inches (1065 mm) high.\n*   **Toe Board:** Must be installed to prevent tools and materials from falling off the edge.\n\n**3. Access and Egress",
